{"id": "duc04-testb-43:0#0", "contents": "Police arrested two journalists, Mufti Abdul Hye and Manzoor Ahmed, editors at the monthly magazine \"Jago Mujahid\" or \"Wake Up Mujahid,\" on charges of writing articles that encouraged Muslim youths to stage an Islamic revolution in Bangladesh, modeled after the Taliban regime in Afghanistan. The journalists were subsequently jailed for a month following their arrest on Wednesday. The arrest was made under a 1974 law that grants police the authority to detain individuals for offenses related to national security, without the need for a court trial for up to three months."}
